headline.main: Outgoing French President Hollande Says 'Ultimate Duty' Is to Prevent Le Pen Victory
headline.print_headline: Outgoing French President Hollande Says 'Ultimate Duty' Is to Prevent Le Pen Victory

lead_paragraph: Outgoing French President Francois Hollande said in European newspaper interviews published on Monday that his "ultimate duty" was to prevent a victory of far-right National Front leader Marine Le Pen in this year's election.
